name: Poha
instructions: Rinse poha and drain. Sauté mustard seeds, curry leaves, onion, potatoes, and green chilies. Add poha, turmeric, and salt. Garnish with coriander and lemon juice.

name: Vada Pav
instructions: Make spiced mashed potato balls, coat with besan batter, and deep-fry. Serve in pav with chutneys.

name: Batata Vada
instructions: Prepare spiced mashed potatoes, form balls, dip in besan batter, and deep-fry until golden.

name: Kanda Bhaji
instructions: Mix sliced onions with besan and spices. Deep-fry spoonfuls of the mixture until crispy.

name: Thalipeeth
instructions: Knead dough with spices and vegetables. Flatten into discs and roast on tawa with oil.

name: Upma
instructions: Sauté mustard seeds, curry leaves, and onions. Add vegetables, roast semolina, and cook with water.

name: Shrikhand
instructions: Whisk hung curd with sugar, saffron, and cardamom. Garnish with nuts and chill before serving.

name: Modak
instructions: Prepare coconut-jaggery filling, stuff in rice flour dough, shape modaks, and steam them.

name: Aluchi Patal Bhaji
instructions: Cook colocasia leaves with besan, jaggery, tamarind, and peanuts to make a tangy curry.

name: Bhakri
instructions: Make dough from jowar flour, flatten into discs, and cook on tawa until done.
